{
  "message": "chore: move spec-evolution visualization Python pipeline into scripts/visualization/\n\nEight Python scripts at the repo root form the build pipeline that\nturns the raw spec-evolution data into the final HTML shipped to\nCloudflare Pages. They are real, but their root-level placement made\nthem indistinguishable from ad-hoc scratch and contributed to the\n\"messy root\" appearance. They form a coherent module and belong under\nscripts/ alongside the deploy and verify helpers.\n\nPipeline stages, in dependency order:\n\n- debug_viz.py: prints diagnostic counts and bucket distributions out\n  of spec_evolution_v1.sqlite3.\n- enhance_viz.py and enhance_viz_final.py: inject enhanced CSS\n  (glassmorphism, animations, color tokens) into the visualization\n  HTML.\n- refactor_viz.py: structural HTML rewrite (~20 KB of edits) for the\n  current visualization layout.\n- fix_viz_errors.py: post-pass cleanup for known parse/markup errors.\n- reapply_enhancements.py: re-runs enhancements after a regen so that\n  manual CSS tweaks survive.\n- finalize_viz.py: final pre-deploy pass; this is the script package.json's\n  build step expects to have already run.\n- restore_full_viz.py: 72 KB recovery script that rebuilds the full\n  visualization from scratch when an enhancement pipeline fails. The\n  script knows which HTML scaffolding lines are load-bearing \u2014 it\n  hardcodes references to frankentui.css, og-image.png, twitter-image.png,\n  and levenshtein_bytes.wasm at the workspace root.\n\nAll scripts read INPUT_FILE = \"visualization_of_..._inception.html\" via\na relative path. After this move, they must be invoked from the\nworkspace root rather than from the new directory:\n\n  # before:\n  python enhance_viz_final.py\n  # after (run from repo root):\n  python scripts/visualization/enhance_viz_final.py\n\nThis is consistent with how every other script under scripts/ is\nalready documented (`./scripts/coverage.sh`, etc.) and with the\nverify_bd_*.sh family that all assume CWD = repo root.\n\nNo automation in the repo currently invokes these scripts (they are\noperator-driven tools), so the move requires no other code changes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
